NOTICE OF HEARING ON CLAIM CONSTRUCTION (MARKMAN HEARING). The Court hereby notifies the parties that the Markman Hearing in the above-captioned matter is confirmed for:

DATE: Wednesday, January 28, 2026
TIME: 9:00 a.m.
LOCATION: Courtroom 4, 5th Floor
         Robert F. Peckham Federal Building
         280 South 1st Street
         San Jose, California 95113
BEFORE: The Honorable Margaret L. Strauss

HEARING PROCEDURES:

1. Each side will be allotted 90 minutes for oral argument on claim construction, inclusive of any technology tutorial.

2. The parties are encouraged to use demonstrative exhibits, including claim charts, annotated patent figures, and technology tutorials. All demonstrative exhibits must be exchanged between the parties no later than January 24, 2026.

3. If either party intends to present live expert testimony at the hearing, notice must be provided to the Court and opposing counsel by January 21, 2026. Telephonic or video testimony will not be permitted.

4. The parties shall submit a joint claim construction chart identifying the agreed-upon and disputed claim terms, with each party's proposed construction and supporting evidence, no later than January 24, 2026.

5. The Court has reviewed the parties' claim construction briefs (Dkt. Nos. 72, 79, 83, 84) and the supporting declarations and exhibits. The Court's questions for the parties, if any, will be communicated in a separate order.

TERMS AT ISSUE:

Based on the parties' Joint Claim Construction Statement (Dkt. No. 68), the following terms remain in dispute:

1. "thermal compression boundary layer" (Claims 1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13)
2. "multi-stage compression molding" (Claims 1, 7, 14)

The parties have agreed on the construction of all other claim terms.

IT IS SO ORDERED.

Signed by Judge Margaret L. Strauss on 1/15/2026.

